title: In Europe-U.S. Clash on Privacy, a Longstanding Schism
text:
08 In Europe-U.S. Clash on Privacy, a Longstanding Schism 
The New York Times: American and European officials working on a new agreement for the international transfer of digital data like social media posts and online search queries are at an impasse after two years of negotiations. And each side has the same excuse: It’s the other’s fault.
